Computer networking is very important in modern technology, enabling the interconnected systems that power the internet, buisness communications, and everyday digital interactions. understanding the fundamentals of computer networking is essential for anyone involved in tectnology, from enthusiasts to professionals. this article will explore the basics of computer networking, including network types, components, protocols, and essentials services like the domain neme system(dns).
what is a computer network
a computer network is a collection of interconnected devices that share resources and information. these devices can include computer, servers, and other hardware. networks allow for the efficient exchange of data, enabling various applications such as email, file sharing, and internet browsing.
how does a computer network work
basics building blocks of a computer network are nodes and links. a network node can be illustrated as equipment for data communication like a modern, router, etc., or equipment of a data terminal like connecting two computer or more. link
om computer networks can be defined as wire or cables or free space of wireless networks.
the working of computer networks can be simply defined as rules or protocols which help in sending and receiving data via the links allow computer networks to communicate. each device has an ip address. that helps in identifying a device.
